title: Latest Sun Sentinel Golf Results (Sept. 15)
text:
Plenty of golf on the slate for Tuesday in Broward and Palm Beach.
ST. THOMAS GIRLS WIN
It’s not often high school golf matches come down to the final tally to figure out who the winner was.
But that was the case Tuesday in St. Thomas Aquinas’ 193-194 girls win over Douglas.
The Eagles led the Raiders by two strokes after calculating the scores of their first three golfers. It all came down to the scores of Rachel Hines and Carson Abt. Luckily for the Raiders, Hines beat Abt by three strokes.
The Best score of the afternoon came from Douglas’ Amanda Okulanis, who shot a 40. She was backed-up by Natalie Toops’ 44.
JUPITER BOYS WIN
Ryder Sutcliffe and Reece Kornfeld quickly put the early season struggles behind them, as they lead Jupiter to a 143-167 boys golf win over Wellington Tuesday at Wycliffe Country Club.
Shooting 1-under par as a team, the two sophomores matched each other with a score of 35.
In an early-season match against Dwyer, where the Warriors played to a 158-158 draw, Sutcliffe and Kornfeld were not theirselves. Shooting 41 and 43, respectively, Jupiter coach Bruce Wasserman says was an abberation, and expects the duo to shoot closer to Tuesday’s scores the rest of the season.
Cameron Starr also contributed, shooting an even 36, while Jason Gizze was 1-over with a 37.
